<P>
IN DALLAS, A STORK IS BORN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the Dallas Zoo, people delivered the stork. 
</P>
<P>
 Zookeepers helped hatch the first saddled-billed stork born in captivity.The 
chick, which was born Thursday, weighed about 3.5 ounces. 
</P>
<P>
 It had been impossible to breed saddle-billed storks in zoos because the 
clipped wings that kept them in open aviaries also prevented successful mating, 
officials said. Nets put on the aviaries now keep the birds in and allow 
breeding. 
</P>
