<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: SAN DIEGO COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Big Park: A private property owner's desire to contribute 80 acres of land 
toward a massive and controversial new San Diego County regional park by Dec. 
31 -- in time to qualify for a tax write-off -- comes under scrutiny this week. 
Landowner Perrin & American wants to donate land in the San Pasqual Valley area 
southeast of Escondido.The proposed San Dieguito Regional Park would stretch 
for 55 miles along the San Dieguito River from the Pacific Ocean at Del Mar 
eastward to Ramona. The issue comes before the San Dieguito River Valley Joint 
Powers Authority at 9:30 a.m. Tuesday at 1500 State St. in San Diego. The 
authority, formed in 1989 by six county governmental bodies with a mandate to 
create the regional park, has faced opposition from a group of landowners, 
Citizens for Private Property Rights. The landowners want their property 
eliminated from the area in which the JPA exercises condemnation powers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
