BRIEFLY: RETAILING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MasterCard Weekly Retail Activity Up Sharply: MasterCard International said 
its U.S. sales authorizations totaled $4.16 billion for the week ended Friday, 
up 28.5% from a year ago.The company said on a percentage basis, sales at 
discount stores and mail order retailers gained most sharply. Discount stores 
tallied $5 million in sales, up 56%, and mail order retailers $5.8 million, up 
51.4%, it said. It said sales authorizations for the holiday season so far 
totaled $11.98 billion, up 29.5% from last year. 
</P>
