<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seoul to Deregulate Petroleum Prices: The country said it will phase out the 
regulations and take other measures soon to lift controls over the petroleum 
industry. The Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy said companies will be 
able to set prices as soon as the second half of next year. The petroleum 
import and export business, now open only to refiners, will soon be open to 
other companies, including foreign ones, the ministry said. 
</P>
