<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; ORANGE COAST HOLDS ON, BEATS L.A. TRADE 
TECH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast scored only eight points in the final 10 minutes but hung on for 
a 67-66 victory over Los Angeles Trade Tech on Sunday in the consolation 
championship of the Coast women's basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 OCC led, 67-66, with 23 seconds left and had a chance to increase the lead, 
but Flo Luppani missed the front end of a one-and-one situation. 
</P>
<P>
 OCC's America Robledo then stole a pass and teammate Tina Afan got the ball 
and started to drive toward the basket. She was fouled with five seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 But Afan miss her free throw, and Trade Tech (7-5) got the rebound and tried 
to get the ball past half court before calling a timeout. But the clock ran out 
as several Trade Tech players and both coaches were frantically screaming for a 
timeout. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates (13-3) opened a 61-55 lead when Robledo made a layup with 9:46, 
left but didn't score again for close to five minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates' next points came when Luppani (11 points) made a three-pointer 
with 4:51 left to put OCC ahead, 64-57. 
</P>
<P>
 Kathleen Kelly had a team-high 19 for Orange Coast, including scoring the 
first six points of the second half to put the Pirates ahead, 52-41. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Shine had 14 points and nine rebounds and Robledo had 12 points for OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 82, Southwestern 45 -- Magdalene Gorska made eight of 13 from the 
field and finished with 18 points for Saddleback. She and teammate Shannon 
Nelson had 11 rebounds each. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
