</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 HURT AS CAR STRIKES POLE, CYCLIST HITS DOWNED LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A motorcyclist was injured Sunday in the aftermath of a traffic accident in 
which a car ran off the road and knocked down a telephone pole, authorities 
said. Two people in the car were hurt. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred at 8:22 a.m. when the auto went off the west side of 
Bouquet Canyon Road and sheared off the pole, said Capt. Mike Flocks of the Los 
Angeles County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Moments later, one of two motorcycle riders coming from the opposite direction 
was knocked off his bike when he ran into the power lines across the road, 
Flocks said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both people in the car were airlifted to area hospitals, said Jeff Ziegler, a 
fire dispatcher. One victim was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission 
Hills. The other was transported to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in 
Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorcycle rider was taken to Newhall Memorial by ambulance, Flocks said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
