<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN KILLED IN CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Compton men were killed and a third escaped uninjured in a car crash early 
Sunday on the Antelope Valley Freeway east of Agua Dulce, California Highway 
Patrol officers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Aldo Lujan, 22, and Eliazar Quintero, 22, were killed when Lujan lost control 
of their vehicle about 3 a.m. while driving south on the freeway near Escondido 
Canyon Road, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
 The car hit the center divider, overturned and rolled, ejecting Lujan and 
Quintero, who was a passenger in the back seat. Raymundo Morales, also 22, from 
Compton, was riding in the front seat and was not hurt, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
 None of the three men in the car were wearing seat belts, officers said. 
</P>
