<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; CIVIC CENTER BEDECKED BY SCOUTS FOR 
HOLIDAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Hall and the youth and community centers have taken on a festive look 
thanks to more than 200 Girl Scouts who painted the windows with holiday bells, 
wreaths and other decorations. 
</P>
<P>
 Brownies, juniors and cadets painted the windows last week as part of an 
annual tradition to decorate the Civic Center for the holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the participants were Done Geer, Brittany Jones, Ginny Geer and Kristi 
Jones, members of Brownie Troop 1983, who decorated windows at City Hall.Pam 
Geer coordinated the event.BERT ELJERA 
</P>
