<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LA PALMA; PURCHASE OF FOUR NEW POLICE CARS OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has approved the purchase of four replacement police vehicles 
at a total cost of $69,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The council, without debate and by unanimous vote, responded to a written 
request by Police Chief David Barr. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Pamela Gibson noted that the city's 1994-95 budget, approved last 
summer, includes $69,000 for the cars. She said they will be bought through a 
mass-volume order coordinated by Los Angeles County. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
