COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; SADDLEBACK COLLEGE TAKING SPRING QUARTER 
APPLICANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Registration for the spring semester at Saddleback College is under way. 
</P>
<P>
 New students may turn in applications with the school's admissions office 
until Thursday, then again beginning Jan. 3, after winter recess. All new 
students must submit an application to get a registration appointment time. 
</P>
<P>
 Continuing students who may have missed their telephone registration 
appointment or want to add or drop a course may do so beginning Jan. 9. 
</P>
<P>
 The college's Office of Admission and Records is open 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. Monday 
through Thursday and 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Friday. The college is at 28000 
Marguerite Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 Spring course schedules are available by calling (714) 582-4530.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
