<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SCHOOL BOARD SPLITS ON VOTES FOR OFFICERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trustees of the Saddleback Valley Unified School District, who have been badly 
split over ideology in the past two years, remained divided last week -- this 
time as a bare majority selected the new board president. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees voted 3 to 2 Tuesday to elect Marcia L. Birch as president.Trustees 
also voted 3 to 2 to elect Bobbee Cline vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees Debbie Hughes and Frank L. Ury tried unsuccessfully for the top two 
spots, but both votes failed 2 to 3. 
</P>
<P>
 The pair had backed two Christian conservative candidates who lost in the Nov. 
8 election while challenging Cline and Dore J. Gilbert, who was named board 
secretary after serving as president. 
</P>
<P>
 Before Birch was elected by her colleagues, Hughes nominated Ury for board 
president, contending that he had the most experience in financial matters as 
the district tries to deal with the county's financial troubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Ury later nominated Hughes for the post of vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 Supt. Peter A. Hartman told the audience that although trustees have been 
divided in the past two years, they are united in helping the district cope 
with the county's bond crisis. JEFF BEANSADDLEBACK VALLE 
</P>
</TEXT>
