COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: DANA POINT; CLOSED SESSION SET ON COUNTY FISCAL CRISIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council will hold a closed session tonight regarding the county 
bankruptcy crisis.Council members will discuss possible legal remedies in 
challenging the county's bankruptcy filing, which has frozen $15.9 million the 
city deposited in the county investment pool. 
</P>
<P>
 The council will also consider hiring special legal counsel to represent the 
city. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be held in an administrative conference room in City Hall at 
6:30 p.m. City Clerk Sharon L. Waits said the council will not be announcing 
the results of the closed-door meeting in council chambers. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about the closed-door session, call (714) 248-9890.FRANK 
MESSINA 
