<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES' ALL-COUNTY FOOTBALL TEAM HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Melsby and Matt Motherway received the top awards as The Times Orange 
County honored its all-county football first-team members, parents and coaches 
at an awards breakfast Sunday at the Hyatt Regency Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 Melsby, a senior wide receiver/defensive back at Los Alamitos, was selected 
back of the year after finishing his prep career as the county's leader in 
career receptions (185), yardage (2,979) and touchdown receptions (35). The 
Griffins were 39-1-1 and won two division championships during his three years 
on the varsity. 
</P>
<P>
 Motherway, a senior offensive and defensive lineman at Mater Dei, was selected 
lineman of the year after helping the undefeated Monarchs win the Division I 
championship. He was a two-time All-South Coast League selection and a 
three-year letterman. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Visser, who led Chapman's return to college football this past season, was 
the guest speaker. Visser came to the Panthers after a three-year stint at 
Whittier College. He also served 13 years as an assistant coach at Long Beach 
State. 
</P>
<P>
 Visser was head coach at Servite from 1974-78, during which time his teams 
shut out their opponents 23 times in 52 games. He led the Friars to the Big 
Five division championship game in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
 The first team: 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive lineman Zane Champion (Trabuco Hills), punter Peter Crosser 
(Servite), linebacker Tony D'Amato (Villa Park), offensive lineman Kris Farris 
(Santa Margarita), quarterback Kevin Feterik (Los Alamitos), running back 
Dahrin Footman (Esperanza). 
</P>
<P>
 Tight end Brian Forth (Esperanza), offensive lineman Jason Grain (Sonora), 
offensive lineman Jeff Hagstrom (Irvine), defensive back Anton Hector 
(Esperanza), defensive lineman Dax Houston (Los Alamitos), defensive back Greg 
Jacobs (Canyon). 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive lineman Bill Johns (Newport Harbor), defensive back Bryan 
Lachappelle (Edison), linebacker Dan McDonough (Newport Harbor), running back 
Brendan McGraw (Laguna Hills), wide receiver Brad Melsby (Los Alamitos), 
offensive lineman Matt Motherway (Mater Dei). 
</P>
<P>
 Wide receiver Rod Perry (Mater Dei), offensive lineman Brett Samperi (San 
Clemente), kicker Patrick Shinnefield (Mater Dei), defensive back Ape Tuato 
(Los Amigos), defensive lineman Tony Tuioti (Foothill), linebacker Chris Young 
(Rancho Alamitos). 
</P>
<P>
 Coach of the Year -- John Barnes (Los Alamitos). 
</P>
</TEXT>
